# Community Contracts v2.1.2

Turn Stardew Valley into a thriving cooperative economy by partnering with townspeople through contracts, automation, and on‑demand services. Version 2.1.2 is the most polished, player‑friendly release yet — removing dialogue interruptions, improving navigation, expanding services, and making it easier than ever to hire the right NPC for the job.

## Getting Started

    Install SMAPI if you haven’t already.
    Download and install Community Contracts.
    Launch Stardew Valley and press V to open the Community Contracts Toolbar.
    You can change the hotkey anytime from the Settings Menu on the toolbar.
    All features, services, and configuration options are accessible directly from the toolbar.

## What’s New in v2.1.2
### Dialogue Interruptions Removed

All services are now accessed exclusively through the toolbar, meaning:

    No more clicking on NPCs to request services
    No more pop‑up dialogues interrupting gameplay
    No more breaking conversations with villagers

This makes the entire system smoother, faster, and far more immersive.
### New Settings Menu + Improved Toolbar Navigation

The toolbar has been redesigned for clarity and speed:

    A dedicated Settings Menu is now accessible directly from the toolbar
    Hotkeys, service options, and mod preferences can be adjusted instantly
    Navigation between menus is cleaner and more intuitive

### All NPCs Now Appear in the Character Menu

Every villager capable of gaining friendship — including modded NPCs — now appears in the Character Menu and can be hired for services.
The Character Menu now displays:

    NPC Level
    Friendship Points
    Sorted automatically from highest → lowest friendship

This makes it incredibly easy to choose the best worker for each job.
### Animal Product Processing Service

Hire a character to process:

    Eggs → Mayo
    Milk → Cheese
    Wool → Cloth
    Truffles → Oil

Features:

    Quality matches the raw goods
    Pulls items from your backpack and autograbbers
    Works across all farm buildings

### Juicing Service

Hire a character to turn:

    Fruit
    Vegetables
    Select forageables

…into juice.
Details:

    Juice quality matches raw goods
    Output quantity scales with item value
    Always profitable when sold
    Uses items from your backpack

### Direct Delivery to the Shipping Bin

For all raw‑goods processing services, you can now choose:

    Deliver finished products to your Delivery Chest, or
    Deliver directly to the Shipping Bin for next‑day profit

### Multiple Workers for Large Jobs

Some services now support multiple NPCs working simultaneously, dramatically speeding up large tasks on big farms.
This is especially useful for:

    Large harvests
    Big processing batches
    High‑volume automation tasks

### Expanded Language Support (Now 11 Languages)
Community Contracts now supports all of the following languages:

    English
    French
    Italian
    German
    Spanish
    Portuguese‑BR
    Russian
    Japanese
    Korean
    Turkish (new in v2.1.2)
    Hungarian (new in v2.1.2)

This brings full support for all official Stardew Valley languages.

## Existing Features from v2.1.1 (Still Included)

### Farming Services

    Planting
    Tilling
    Watering
    Garden Pot placement
    Bee House placement
    Honey collection + optional mead processing
    Animal care
    Seed making

### Other Services

    Sashimi making
    Ore processing
    Tapper installation

    Reliable crop harvesting
    Smarter crab pot placement, baiting, and harvesting
    Adjustable rectangular service areas

### Core Systems

    Delivery chest with customizable colors and labels
    Contract growth tied to friendship and skill
    Specialist and non‑specialist NPC roles
    Optional processor time reduction

## Summary
Community Contracts v2.1.2 is the most refined version yet — eliminating dialogue interruptions, improving navigation, expanding automation, and making NPC hiring smarter and more intuitive. Whether you’re running a small homestead or a massive industrial farm, this update makes the entire system smoother, faster, and more immersive.
